Building up a set of documents I frequently put in question marks for something yet to be written - purely for editing purposes. I happened to have a document I wanted to look at using Netsurf with the following temporary mark up
&lt;p&gt;&lt;object class="flt" title="?????"  type="image/png"
data="../pics/????????????.png"&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;????????????&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;/object&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

Netsurf \(12 Sep build\) seems to use the question marks as a wild-card for file names as it picked up an actual image which happened to have 12 characters before the full stop. If I altered the number of question marks it found a different file.

I'm certain that this isn't meant to happen - rather the object content should be rendered - which happens if I name a fle \(without question marks\) which happens not to exist - as I would expect.

Keith Hopper
asgard@inspire.net.nz

